[debug] [2026-03-24T23:48:54.436Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/going-5d1ae/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-03-24T23:48:54.436Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/going-5d1ae/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Here are 4 GraphQL operations for your app, with proper authentication as per the guidelines:\n\n1.  **Retrieve all available rides:** This query is publicly accessible, allowing any user to view available rides.\n\n    ```graphql\n    query GetAllRides @auth(level: PUBLIC, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to the public\") {\n      rides {\n        id\n        driver {\n          displayName\n        }\n        departureCity\n        destinationCity\n        departureDateTime\n        availableSeats\n        pricePerSeat\n      }\n    }\n    ```\n\n2.  **Get a user's own bookings:** This query allows a logged-in user to see their personal ride bookings. It uses `auth.uid` to filter the bookings, ensuring data privacy.\n\n    ```graphql\n    query GetMyBookings @auth(level: USER) {\n      bookings(where: {passengerId: {eq_expr: \"auth.uid\"}}) {\n        id\n        ride {\n          departureCity\n          destinationCity\n          departureDateTime\n        }\n        seatsBooked\n        totalPrice\n        bookingStatus\n      }\n    }\n    ```\n\n3.  **Create a new ride booking:** This mutation allows a logged-in user to create a new booking for a ride. It uses `auth.uid` to associate the booking with the correct passenger.\n\n    ```graphql\n    mutation CreateBooking($rideId: UUID!, $seatsBooked: Int!, $totalPrice: Float!) @auth(level: USER) {\n      booking_insert(data: {\n        passengerId_expr: \"auth.uid\",\n        rideId: $rideId,\n        seatsBooked: $seatsBooked,\n        totalPrice: $totalPrice,\n        bookingStatus: \"PENDING\",\n        createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n      })\n    }\n    ```\n\n4.  **Update a user's profile information:** This mutation lets a logged-in user update their own display name and bio. It uses `auth.uid` to ensure only the authenticated user can modify their profile.\n\n    ```graphql\n    mutation UpdateMyProfile($displayName: String!, $bio: String) @auth(level: USER) {\n      user_update(key: {id_expr: \"auth.uid\"}, data: {\n        displayName: $displayName,\n        bio: $bio\n      })\n    }\n    ```\n\nHere are some follow-up questions you might consider:\n\n*   How can I add more complex filtering or ordering to the `GetAllRides` query?\n*   What is the best practice for handling errors when creating a booking, especially if the `seatsBooked` exceeds `availableSeats`?\n*   Can I retrieve the driver's details along with the ride information in the `GetMyBookings` query?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
[debug] [2026-03-24T23:48:57.430Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/going-5d1ae/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-03-24T23:48:57.430Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/going-5d1ae/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Alright, let's get your database seeded with some initial data! Firebase Data Connect makes it easy to set up your app's starting point.\n\nTo populate your database, we'll create a single mutation that inserts multiple entries into your `User`, `Ride`, and `Booking` tables. This `seedDemoData` mutation will use hardcoded values, which is perfect for development and testing. I'll also add a `@transaction` directive to ensure that all these inserts either fully succeed or completely fail, maintaining data integrity.\n\nHere's the GraphQL mutation:\n\n```graphql\nmutation seedDemoData @transaction @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This mutation inserts demo data and is safe to execute by any logged-in user.\") {\n  user_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"b2d07584-6e69-42c2-841f-0e1f6e2b1c3d\",\n      displayName: \"Alice Smith\",\n      email: \"alice.smith@example.com\",\n      phoneNumber: \"+15551234567\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-26T10:00:00Z\",\n      bio: \"Avid traveler looking for carpooling adventures.\",\n      carMake: \"Toyota\",\n      carModel: \"Corolla\",\n      licensePlate: \"ABC123\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"f3a9e6d0-4b8c-4c7a-9f5e-1d2a3b4c5d6e\",\n      displayName: \"Bob Johnson\",\n      email: \"bob.johnson@example.com\",\n      phoneNumber: \"+15559876543\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-26T10:05:00Z\",\n      bio: \"Commuter offering rides to work.\",\n      carMake: \"Honda\",\n      carModel: \"Civic\",\n      licensePlate: \"DEF456\"\n    }\n  ])\n  ride_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-1234-567890abcdef\",\n      driverId: \"b2d07584-6e69-42c2-841f-0e1f6e2b1c3d\",\n      departureCity: \"New York\",\n      destinationCity: \"Boston\",\n      departureDateTime: \"2023-11-15T08:00:00Z\",\n      availableSeats: 3,\n      pricePerSeat: 25.00,\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-26T10:10:00Z\",\n      notes: \"Luggage space available.\",\n      carInfo: \"Blue Toyota Corolla\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"b9a8c7d6-e5f4-3210-fedc-ba9876543210\",\n      driverId: \"f3a9e6d0-4b8c-4c7a-9f5e-1d2a3b4c5d6e\",\n      departureCity: \"Los Angeles\",\n      destinationCity: \"San Francisco\",\n      departureDateTime: \"2023-11-20T14:30:00Z\",\n      availableSeats: 2,\n      pricePerSeat: 50.00,\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-26T10:15:00Z\",\n      notes: \"Snacks and water provided.\",\n      carInfo: \"Silver Honda Civic\"\n    }\n  ])\n  booking_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"c1d2e3f4-a5b6-7c8d-9e0f-1a2b3c4d5e6f\",\n      passengerId: \"f3a9e6d0-4b8c-4c7a-9f5e-1d2a3b4c5d6e\",\n      rideId: \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-1234-567890abcdef\",\n      seatsBooked: 1,\n      totalPrice: 25.00,\n      bookingStatus: \"CONFIRMED\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-26T10:20:00Z\",\n      paymentTransactionId: \"PAYID12345\"\n    }\n  ])\n}\n```\n\nThis mutation will:\n1. Create two `User` entries.\n2. Create two `Ride` entries, referencing the previously created users as drivers.\n3. Create one `Booking` entry, linking one of the users as a passenger to one of the rides.\n\nTo learn more about seeding data and bulk operations, you could ask:\n\n*   How can I reset this seed data to a zero state for testing?\n*   What are the best practices for handling foreign key references in seed data mutations?\n*   Can I generate this type of mutation using AI assistance in the Firebase console?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
